{
  "texts": [
    "Some experts have also argued for the use of hybrid models that, in addition to using stochastic deep learning techniques, employ classical AI, which relies on symbolic representations of concepts to mimic the way humans learn and reason.",
    "3 This may involve encoding pathophysiologic principles, diagnostic frameworks, and illness scripts into LLMs.",
    "In health care, the rationale by which a model arrives at its output may be as important as the output itself.",
    "Models that can provide the motivations for their responses-that can \"show their work\"-may be critical for their adoption, effectiveness, and fairness, as well as knowing when human decision-makers should deviate from a model's recommendations, and why.",
    "In 2021, the National Institute of Standards and Technology developed principles for explainable AI, including that models provide explanations for their outputs with evidence, accuracy, meaning (i.e., they are readily understood), and caution (i.e., they identify and declare the limits of their knowledge)."
  ]
}